# WebAnalytics SaaS — Build Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A fully functional, deployable Google Analytics-style SaaS platform with:
- **Landing page** — hero, feature cards, CTAs
- **Auth** — register + login with bcrypt passwords and JWT httpOnly cookies
- **Dashboard** — 5 separate analytics sections driven by real GA4 Data API
- **Google OAuth2** — "Connect Google Analytics" consent flow, refresh token stored in SQLite
- **Server** — Node.js + Express serving both API and frontend from port 3000

---

## Project Structure (23 files)

```
WebAnalytics/
├── backend/
│   ├── server.js          ← Express entry point (await DB init → listen)
│   ├── package.json       ← sql.js, bcryptjs, jwt, @google-analytics/data, etc.
│   ├── .env               ← Google credentials + JWT secret
│   ├── db/
│   │   ├── schema.sql     ← users + websites tables
│   │   └── database.js    ← sql.js with better-sqlite3-compatible API wrapper
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   └── authMiddleware.js  ← JWT verification
│   └── routes/
│       ├── auth.js        ← register, login, logout, /me
│       ├── google.js      ← OAuth2 /connect + /callback
│       ├── websites.js    ← CRUD for GA4 properties
│       └── analytics.js   ← GA4 proxy: realtime, overview, audience, acquisition, behavior
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html         ← Landing/marketing page
    ├── login.html
    ├── register.html
    ├── dashboard.html     ← SPA with 5 analytics sections + settings
    ├── css/
    │   ├── style.css      ← Design tokens, components, tables, modals
    │   ├── auth.css       ← Animated glassmorphism auth cards
    │   └── dashboard.css  ← Sidebar, KPI cards, chart containers
    └── js/
        ├── api.js         ← Fetch wrapper + auth guard
        ├── auth.js        ← Login/register form logic
        ├── charts.js      ← Chart.js wrappers (line, doughnut, bar)
        └── analytics.js   ← GA4 data fetcher + chart/table renderer
```

