## How to Start the Server

```powershell
cd C:\Users\oblivora\OneDrive\Desktop\WebAnalytics\backend
node server.js
# or for dev with auto-restart:
npx nodemon server.js
```

---

## Deployment Notes

When deploying to a server (Render, Railway, VPS, etc.):
1. Update [.env](file:///C:/Users/oblivora/OneDrive/Desktop/WebAnalytics/backend/.env) → set `REDIRECT_URI` and `FRONTEND_URL` to your production domain
2. Update the **Authorized redirect URIs** in Google Cloud Console to match
3. The SQLite database (`db/analytics.db`) persists on disk — for production consider mounting a persistent volume or switching to PostgreSQL (swap `sql.js` for `pg`)
